But medical school had not
prepared me to do that.

00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:21.313
Not even slightly.

00:29:22.870 --> 00:29:25.840
I went to Berkeley and
got a public health degree

00:29:25.840 --> 00:29:27.700
because I knew I needed those skills,

00:29:27.700 --> 00:29:30.220
and then I was graced with Sherri Sager

00:29:30.220 --> 00:29:32.930
and Lucy Crane coming
into my life, both of whom

00:29:32.930 --> 00:29:33.820
took me to Sacramento.

